channel.description:
Have SRL folder in incldues folder
Getting and Invalid Perimeter? Wait for the next version of SRL...
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SRL Logger by SDCIT
I have nothing to put here
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
This script is designed to cut a whole inventory of wood (any type) and drop it all. It was suppose to give an option of lighting the wood instead, but i dicided not to include that FOR NOW for many reasons. One of the reasons was that i may make this a pay script. THIS IS BETA. It IS FLAWED IN SOME WAYS!. Report any flaws + suggstion. Its been so long since i made a script for RS... -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Instructions.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 1. Use epacsenur Client Low Detail. 2. Set your Screen to 32 bit TRUE color. 3. Position your Player[s] anywhere with trees. 4. Have axe in first inv slot. 5. Color pick what the script has in its const. 6. FIll out the other stuff
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Features.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- - SRL Based. - Good way of gaining woodcutting levels. - Auto Handling Randoms. - Logout from New Box. - VERY COOL RANDOM TAB
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Known Issues.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- - You tell me. - May miss a tree and hang (RARELY) - ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Version History: ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- v 1.111- Put on SRL got rid of some stuff.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- General Notice: -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Use this script at your own risk. I'm NOT responsible for any Ban or Loss you might encounter using this script.
Scar Resource Library rev 222+ (scripted on dev's version) NAME : SRLLOGGER BETA WRITER : Sdcit CATEGORY : PowerCutter DESCRIPTION : Cuts wood? USAGE : START ANYWHERE AUTOCOLOR : No. COLORPICK THE TREE COLORS! NOTES : I will include the SPOWER cutter for those of you that like collecting OLD scripts
WHY NO AUTOCOLORS?
Well, i originally used a Findobj and getcolor thing, but it messed up 99% of the time.
NEXT UPDATE:
1. AutoColors 2. Lighting feature (MAYBE)

item.title: SRL logger
item.dc:creator: @Pwnd Pwnd
item.description:
@Pwnd wrote:

Your code made me want to cry, but, luckily, I surpressed that emotion for the time being.

{/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
                 Pwnd's super-leet clean code, wewt!
{////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////}
program SRLLogger;
{.include SRL/SRL.scar}
{.include SRL/SRL/Skill/WoodCutting.scar}
{.include SRL/SRL/Skill/FireMaking.scar}
{.include SRL/SRL/Misc/CerterBreaker.scar}

var
  Waits, T1, T2, T3, q, Loges, Loa:Integer;
  T:Array [1..3] of Integer;
{<----------------------SETUP?------------------->}

const
  StartPlayer    = 0;
  MaxWait        = 2;     // wood click interval. In seconds.
  Loads          = 0;     // Number of loads before switching Player.
  Play           = 2;     // how many players you wish to use. Remember
                             // change the player array to fit it.
  Light          = false; // True to light logs, false to drop
  LoginWait      = 600;   // time to wait before logging in again in seconds.

///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
{              COLORS:         AutoColors in next update ;)                      }
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
     
const
  TreeC          = 3240032;    // TreeColor 1
  TreeC2         = 1654844;     // TreeColor 2
  TreeC3         = 1779752;    // Treecolor 3
  Bark           = 2045510;   // trees bark color
     
////////////////////////////Color SEtup^///////////////////////////////////




procedure DeclarePlayers;
begin
  HowManyPlayers:= Play;

  NumberOfPlayers(HowManyPlayers); // set arraylength

  Players[0].Name :='starshark';
  Players[0].Pass :='sdf';
  Players[0].Nick :='tar';
  Players[0].Loc  :='AnyWhere';
  Players[0].Active:= true;

  Players[1].Name :='Sdcit';
  Players[1].Pass :='asdfwer';
  Players[1].Nick :='cit';
  Players[1].Loc  :='Lumbridge';
  Players[1].Active:= true;

end;

procedure Arrays;
begin
  T[1]:= T1;
  T[2]:= T2;
  T[3]:= T3;
end;

{*******************************************************************************
procedure HoverSkill;
By: Dankness
Description: Hovers mouse over selected skill to "check exp"
*******************************************************************************}

procedure hoverskill(skill: string);
var
  row, col: integer;
begin
  case lowercase(skill) of
    'attack'     :begin row:=1; col:=1; end;
    'strength'   :begin row:=2; col:=1; end;
    'defence'    :begin row:=3; col:=1; end;
    'range'      :begin row:=4; col:=1; end;
    'prayer'     :begin row:=5; col:=1; end;
    'magic'      :begin row:=6; col:=1; end;
    'runecraft'  :begin row:=7; col:=1; end;
    'hitpoints'  :begin row:=1; col:=2; end;
    'agility'    :begin row:=2; col:=2; end;
    'herblore'   :begin row:=3; col:=2; end;
    'thieving'   :begin row:=4; col:=2; end;
    'crafting'   :begin row:=5; col:=2; end;
    'fletching'  :begin row:=6; col:=2; end;
    'slayer'     :begin row:=7; col:=2; end;
    'smithing'   :begin row:=1; col:=3; end;
    'mining'     :begin row:=2; col:=3; end;
    'fishing'    :begin row:=3; col:=3; end;
    'cooking'    :begin row:=4; col:=3; end;
    'firemaking' :begin row:=5; col:=3; end;
    'woodcutting':begin row:=6; col:=3; end;
    'farming'    :begin row:=7; col:=3; end;
    'random'     :begin row:=random(6)+1; col:=random(2)+1; end;
  end;
  gametab(2);
  if(useBenMouse)then
    mmouse(532 + (64 * col), 191 + (31 * row), 10, 10)
  else
    mmouse2(532 + (64 * col), 191 + (31 * row), 10, 10);
  wait(5000 + random(5000));
end;


procedure BeginRun;
begin
  SetRun(True);
  MouseFindFlag(632, 32, 2, -2);
  Flag;
  wait(10000 + Random(2000));
  MouseFindFlag(656, 132, 2, -2);
  Flag;
end;

procedure RandomTab;
var
  ac, at:Integer;
begin
  ac:= 1 + random(50)
  if(ac <= 7)then
    begin
      GameTab(ac);
      case ac of
        1: SetFightMode(1 + random(3));
        2: hoverskill('random');
        4: UseItem(2 + random(27));
      end;
      wait(3000 + random(2000));
      at:= 1 + random(8);
      GameTab(at);
      wait(3000 + random(2000));
    end;
end;

function DeclareWaitLength(MSI: Integer): Integer;
begin
  Result:= ((1 + Random(MSI)) * 1000) + random(20);
end;

procedure  Rapport;
var
  activity: string;
begin
  writeln('Name         : '+ Players[CurrentPlayer].Name);
  writeln('Number       : '+inttostr(CurrentPlayer));
  writeln('Location     : '+ Players[CurrentPlayer].loc);
  if players[CurrentPlayer].active=true then  activity:= 'true' else  activity:='false';
  writeln('Active       : '+ activity);
  writeln('Cut          : '+ IntToStr(Loges)+' logs')
  writeln('');
  writeln('');
  Writeln('Randoms Report <3 Fakawi    :')
  if(fights > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Fought '+IntToStr(fights)+' Time[s].');
  if(talks > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Talked to '+IntToStr(talks)+' Random event[s].');
  if(lamps > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Used lamps '+IntToStr(lamps)+' Time[s].');
  if(doctors > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Solved '+IntToStr(doctors)+' Fords[s].');
  if(frogs > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Solved '+IntToStr(frogs)+' Frog[s].');
  if(AxeAttaches > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Attached '+IntToStr(AxeAttaches)+' Axes.');
  if(boxes > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Solved '+IntToStr(boxes)+' Box[es].');
  if(demons > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Solved '+IntToStr(demons)+' Demon[s].');
  if(logs > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Logged in '+IntToStr(logs)+' Time[s].');
  if(Certers > 0)then
    WriteLn('  Solved Certers '+IntToStr(Certers)+' Time[s].')
  WriteLn('<=====================================================>');
end;

procedure SetUp;
var
  abcd: Integer;
begin
  abcd:= 5;
  repeat
    Writeln(' The script will start in   : ' + inttostr(abcd) + ' seconds');
    wait(1000)
    abcd:= abcd - 1;
  until(abcd = 0);
  ClearDebug;
  SetUpSRL;
  DisguiseScar('Welcome to CartoonNetwork.com! - Flash Player Installation - Microsoft Internet Explorer');
  LoadFireMakingBitmaps;
  DeclarePlayers;
  CurrentPlayer:= StartPlayer;
  LoginPlayer;       // logs in the first player.
  Reincarnate:=true;
  Arrays;
end;

procedure FindRandoms;
begin
  CloseWindow;
  ClickToContinue;
  FindLamp('mining');
  FindMod;
  FindMime;
  FindCerter;
  FindMaze;
  FindQuiz;
  FindFrog;
  FindDoctor;
  FindBox;
  FindDemon;
  FindForester;
  FindHead;
  FindBirdsNest;
  FindEnt(Bark)
  if(FindFight)then
    Beginrun;
  if(FindNewBox)then
    Logout;
end;

procedure Choper;
begin
  Waits:= DeclareWaitLength(MaxWait);
  if(q = 3)then
    q:= 0;
  q:= 1;
  if(Findcolor(x, y, T[q], 5, 4, 514, 336))then
    begin
      Mmouse(x, y, 0, 0);
      mouse(x, y, 0, 0, true);
      FindRandoms;
      flag;
      if(Getcolor(81,430) = 0)or
        (getcolor(140, 420) = 0)or
        (Getcolor(194,426)=0) then
        begin
          repeat
            FindRandoms;
            wait(Waits + Random(20));
            mouse(x, y, 0, 0, true);
          until(getcolor(77, 407) = 0)
        end else
          randomtab;
  end else
    q:= q + 1;
  Loges:= Loges + 1;
end;

procedure UseToEnd(x: integer);
var
  qwe: Integer;
begin
  for(qwe:= x + 1 to 28)do
    begin
      UseItem(x);
      UseItem(qwe);
    end;
end;

Procedure DropTo(x, y: Integer);
var
   todr: Integer;
begin
  for(todr:= x to y)do
    DropItem(todr);
end;

procedure LC;
begin
  Status('Dropping Logs');
  WriteLn('Dropping Logs');
  DropTo(2, 28);
  Loa:= Loa + 1;
end;

procedure standout;
begin
  repeat
    Wait(1000);
    FindRandoms;
  until(not(LoggedIn));
  NextPlayer(false);
end;

{

[============================================================]
                          Main Line
[============================================================]


}
begin
  SetupDemon;
  T1:= TreeC;
  T2:= TreeC2;
  T3:= TreeC3;
  activateclient;
  SetUp;
  activateclient;
  LogInPlayer;
  repeat
    Loa:= 0;
    SetChat('off', 1);
    SetChat('off', 2);
    SetChat('off', 3);
    NickNameBMP:= CreateBitmapMaskFromText(Players[CurrentPlayer].Nick, UpChars)
    GameTab(4)
    Head:= GetColor(590, 220);
    Head2:= GetColor(587, 219);
    Head3:= GetColor(588, 218);
    repeat
      FindRandoms;
      if(InvFull)then
        begin
          LC;
        end;
      Choper;
      RandomTab;
      if(not(Loggedin))then
        break;
      if((WeAreDead))then
        standout;
      if(loa >= 1)then
        if(Loads mod loa = 0)then
          begin
            Rapport;
            NextPlayer(true);
            break;
          end;
    until (false)
    if(not(Loggedin))then
      NextPlayer(False);  // Always the last line!
  until(false)
end.
